text: Great job as usual Ryan. But this time please accept a little critics: This video is too much unbalanced to seasides. Clearly you was there during summer, and best way to spend time in Sicilian summer is swimming and snorkeling. In other terms, better stay on the coast. But can't miss in a video like this Erice, fairy tales stone village on the top of the hill, often surrounded by own cloud that means fog in the village, Noto, georgeous Baroque city world heritage, Modica, city inside a canyon famous for the chocolate too, Gangi, pictoresque hill village, voted as best village in Italy in 2014 and Marzamemi, pictoresque and unique fishermann village. About nature, how forget, Vendicari Natural reserve, with beautiful beach Cala Mosche? Of course in a top ten some choices must be made, but these places are a must.
